#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:4
msgid "set_color - set the terminal color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:9
msgid "set_color [OPTIONS] VALUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:16
msgid ""
"``set_color`` is used to control the color and styling of text in the "
"terminal. *VALUE* describes that styling. *VALUE* can be a reserved color "
"name like **red** or an RGB color value given as 3 or 6 hexadecimal digits "
"(\"F27\" or \"FF2277\"). A special keyword **normal** resets text formatting "
"to terminal defaults."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:18
msgid "Valid colors include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:20
msgid ""
"**black**, **red**, **green**, **yellow**, **blue**, **magenta**, **cyan**, "
"**white**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:21
msgid ""
"**brblack**, **brred**, **brgreen**, **bryellow**, **brblue**, "
"**brmagenta**, **brcyan**, **brwhite**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:23
msgid ""
"The *br*- (as in 'bright') forms are full-brightness variants of the 8 "
"standard-brightness colors on many terminals. **brblack** has higher "
"brightness than **black** - towards gray."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:25
msgid ""
"An RGB value with three or six hex digits, such as A0FF33 or f2f can be "
"used. Fish will choose the closest supported color. A three digit value is "
"equivalent to specifying each digit twice; e.g., ``set_color 2BC`` is the "
"same as ``set_color 22BBCC``. Hexadecimal RGB values can be in lower or "
"uppercase. Depending on the capabilities of your terminal (and the level of "
"support ``set_color`` has for it) the actual color may be approximated by a "
"nearby matching reserved color name or ``set_color`` may not have an effect "
"on color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:27
msgid ""
"A second color may be given as a desired fallback color. e.g. ``set_color "
"124212 brblue`` will instruct set_color to use *brblue* if a terminal is not "
"capable of the exact shade of grey desired. This is very useful when an 8 or "
"16 color terminal might otherwise not use a color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:29
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:31
msgid "**-b** or **--background** *COLOR*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:32
msgid "Sets the background color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:34
msgid "**-c** or **--print-colors**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:35
msgid "Prints the given colors or a colored list of the 16 named colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:37
msgid "**-o** or **--bold**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:38
msgid "Sets bold mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:40
msgid "**-d** or **--dim**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:41
msgid "Sets dim mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:43
msgid "**-i** or **--italics**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:44
msgid "Sets italics mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:46
msgid "**-r** or **--reverse**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:47
msgid "Sets reverse mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:49
msgid "**-u** or **--underline**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:50
msgid "Sets underlined mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:52
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:53
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:55
msgid ""
"Using the **normal** keyword will reset foreground, background, and all "
"formatting back to default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:58
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:60
msgid ""
"Using the **normal** keyword will reset both background and foreground "
"colors to whatever is the default for the terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:61
msgid ""
"Setting the background color only affects subsequently written characters. "
"Fish provides no way to set the background color for the entire terminal "
"window. Configuring the window background color (and other attributes such "
"as its opacity) has to be done using whatever mechanisms the terminal "
"provides. Look for a config option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:62
msgid ""
"Some terminals use the ``--bold`` escape sequence to switch to a brighter "
"color set rather than increasing the weight of text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:63
msgid ""
"``set_color`` works by printing sequences of characters to standard output. "
"If used in command substitution or a pipe, these characters will also be "
"captured. This may or may not be desirable. Checking the exit status of "
"``isatty stdout`` before using ``set_color`` can be useful to decide not to "
"colorize output in a script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:66
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:71
msgid ""
"set_color red; echo \"Roses are red\"\n"
"set_color blue; echo \"Violets are blue\"\n"
"set_color 62A; echo \"Eggplants are dark purple\"\n"
"set_color normal; echo \"Normal is nice\" # Resets the background too"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:78
msgid "Terminal Capability Detection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:80
msgid ""
"Fish uses some heuristics to determine what colors a terminal supports to "
"avoid sending sequences that it won't understand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:82
msgid "In particular it will:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:84
msgid ""
"Enable 256 colors if :envvar:`TERM` contains \"xterm\", except for known "
"exceptions (like MacOS 10.6 Terminal.app)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:85
msgid ""
"Enable 24-bit (\"true-color\") even if the $TERM entry only reports 256 "
"colors. This includes modern xterm, VTE-based terminals like Gnome Terminal, "
"Konsole and iTerm2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:86
msgid "Detect support for italics, dim, reverse and other modes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:88
msgid ""
"If terminfo reports 256 color support for a terminal, 256 color support will "
"always be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:90
msgid ""
"To force true-color support on or off, set :envvar:`fish_term24bit` to \"1\" "
"for on and 0 for off - ``set -g fish_term24bit 1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:92
msgid ""
"To debug color palette problems, ``tput colors`` may be useful to see the "
"number of colors in terminfo for a terminal. Fish launched as ``fish -d "
"term_support`` will include diagnostic messages that indicate the color "
"support mode in use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:94
msgid ""
"The ``set_color`` command uses the terminfo database to look up how to "
"change terminal colors on whatever terminal is in use. Some systems have old "
"and incomplete terminfo databases, and lack color information for terminals "
"that support it. Fish assumes that all terminals can use the [ANSI X3.64]"
"(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code) escape sequences if the "
"terminfo definition indicates a color below 16 is not supported."
msgstr ""
